<i>He escaped Puente Grande
in 2001.</i>

36:04.987 --> 36:07.831
<i>He escaped law enforcement
for 13 years.</i>

36:07.990 --> 36:10.250
<i>He escaped us
during our operation,</i>

36:10.409 --> 36:11.910
<i>out of his safe house.</i>

36:11.994 --> 36:15.255
And now you put him
in a maximum-security prison

36:15.339 --> 36:19.250
<i>in Mexico, and you think
that he's going to be secure?</i>

36:19.335 --> 36:20.844
<i>I don't think so.</i>

36:20.928 --> 36:23.504
<i>I think
it was probably inevitable.</i>

36:23.589 --> 36:26.591
<i>I had some initial shock
when he broke out.</i>

36:26.684 --> 36:30.094
<i>But went right back
into "let's go get this guy.</i>

36:30.179 --> 36:31.930
<i>"He's done this before to us.</i>

36:32.014 --> 36:35.192
Let's mount up the team
and get after him."

