41:44.251 --> 41:46.586
I wondered if Chapo
had pulled off

41:46.670 --> 41:48.663
probably the most elaborate
escape possible.

41:48.747 --> 41:50.507
<i>But then the power
comes back on,</i>

41:50.666 --> 41:52.667
<i>and Chapo's sitting right there</i>

41:52.760 --> 41:55.512
<i>at counsel's table, smiling.</i>

41:55.596 --> 42:00.183
<i>- In the end, El Chapo is not
able to escape U.S. justice.</i>

42:00.267 --> 42:02.769
<i>- Chapo Guzmán was convicted
on all counts,</i>

42:02.853 --> 42:06.097
and ultimately he was sentenced
to life plus 30 years,

42:06.181 --> 42:09.776
and he's now residing
in Florence, Colorado,

42:09.935 --> 42:11.361
<i>in the supermax prison.</i>

42:13.438 --> 42:19.110
- Joaquín "El Chapo" Guzmán
is an evil genius.

42:19.194 --> 42:22.121
He ran the biggest
drug cartel in the world,

42:22.281 --> 42:24.448
made billions of dollars,

42:24.542 --> 42:27.293
and organized massive
clandestine operations

42:27.378 --> 42:31.047
to build tunnels, like this one.

42:31.206 --> 42:36.302
His biggest fear--
Landing in U.S. custody.

42:36.387 --> 42:39.547
But today, that's exactly
where he is.

42:39.631 --> 42:42.392
A supermax prison in Colorado

42:42.476 --> 42:47.138
nicknamed the Alcatraz
of the Rockies.

42:47.222 --> 42:50.391
He spends his days
in solitary confinement

42:50.475 --> 42:54.645
and has almost no contact
with the outside world.

42:54.730 --> 42:57.815
Authorities believe
they finally found a prison

42:57.908 --> 43:00.318
he cannot escape.

43:00.402 --> 43:04.247
But with someone like El Chapo,

43:04.406 --> 43:07.250
it's important
to never say "never."
